  "body": "run multiple contract tests: https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/blob/e0d6fff9bd51b4bf769d001f854b19805c150c00/forge/src/multi_runner.rs#L136-L144\r\n\r\nset init_state: https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/blob/e0d6fff9bd51b4bf769d001f854b19805c150c00/forge/src/runner.rs#L111\r\n\r\nreset state before each test: https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/blob/e0d6fff9bd51b4bf769d001f854b19805c150c00/forge/src/runner.rs#L119\r\n\r\n\r\nThe issue arises between test contract 0 -> test contract 1.\r\n\r\ncontract 0:\r\n  set init_state as correct init state\r\n  run tests with good init state\r\n  NO reset state\r\n\r\ncontract 1:\r\n  set new init state *WHICH IS POST test contract 0 state\r\n  run tests with bad init state\r\n  No reset state\r\n\r\nSo the last call of each test contract will affect the next test contract's state",
